---
const gates = [
  {
    n: 1,
    title: 'The call ran long enough to be worth caching',
    paperRef: '§3.3.2 perf guard',
    signal: 'duration_ns ≥ Config.min_duration_s (default 1 s)',
    note: 'Below the threshold, the cache write would cost more than the recomputation. Same idea as the paper’s perf guard; rote also tracks the per-call encode time in `src/rote/purity.py` so a 1 GB return for a trivial call still gets blacklisted.',
  },
  {
    n: 2,
    title: 'The call performed no impure I/O',
    paperRef: '§3.3 + §3.3.1',
    signal:
      'no audit-hook event for network / exec / subprocess; any file opened in `"w"` mode is closed before the call returns',
    note: 'PEP 578 audit hooks (2018) classify network, subprocess, exec, file-append, and unclosed-write opens. A `with open(...): ...` write that closes inside the call is paper §3.3.1’s self-contained write — pure, plus a tracked write-dependency.',
  },
  {
    n: 3,
    title: 'No argument was mutated in place during the call',
    paperRef: 'beyond the paper',
    signal: 'arg fingerprints at entry == arg fingerprints at exit',
    note: 'Copy-on-call hashing: re-fingerprint mutable args at call exit and drop the cache write if anything moved. The paper assumed pure-looking functions were pure; rote catches the in-place list, dict, and DataFrame mutations that static analysis alone wouldn’t spot.',
  },
  {
    n: 4,
    title: 'The source code and its dependencies haven’t changed',
    paperRef: '§3.4 + §3.5',
    signal:
      'blake3(canonical_AST(func) ⊕ transitive_callee_ids ⊕ file_dep_hashes ⊕ global_dep_fingerprints) matches the cached key',
    note: 'libcst’s canonical AST lets cosmetic edits leave the hash steady (the paper invalidated those). Transitive callee ids cover §3.4. file_dep_hashes are the (size, mtime_ns, ctime_ns) plus content-hash table from §3.5; ctime_ns is rote’s addition so a backdated edit still misses.',
  },
];
---

<section id="gates" class="container-wide mt-24 scroll-mt-24" aria-labelledby="gates-h">
  <header class="mb-8 max-w-3xl">
    <p class="eyebrow">08 — Purity model</p>
    <h2 id="gates-h" class="h-section mt-3">
      The four checks a function has to pass to be memoized
    </h2>
    <p class="lede mt-4">
      A refresher on the paper's purity model. Each row shows what the paper required and the
      specific signal rote watches for it. Any single red signal blocks the cache write; the
      reason is logged to <code>rote.stats()["invalidation_reasons"]</code> so missed memoization
      is visible instead of silent.
    </p>
  </header>

  <ol class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
    {gates.map((g) => (
      <li class="group card p-6 transition-colors hover:bg-[var(--color-page-dark)]/40">
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
          <span class="num text-2xl text-[var(--color-rote)]">{String(g.n).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
          <span class="pill pill-paper">{g.paperRef}</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="mt-3 text-lg leading-snug">{g.title}</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 font-mono text-xs text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] whitespace-pre-wrap">
          <Fragment set:html={g.signal.replace(/`([^`]+)`/g, '<code>$1</code>')} />
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">
          <Fragment set:html={g.note.replace(/`([^`]+)`/g, '<code>$1</code>')} />
        </p>
      </li>
    ))}
  </ol>
</section>
